The paper deals with visual dialog, which involves understanding both visual and textual information. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new model for visual reference resolution, which involves attention mechanisms and learning latent relationships, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
